WEBVTT

00:04.254 --> 00:06.296
<i>Since resources are finite,</i>

00:06.297 --> 00:10.135
<i>we need rules for colony entry and exit.</i>

00:10.844 --> 00:12.886
<i>But indiscriminate players like Dhruv</i>

00:12.887 --> 00:17.267
<i>can't be let outside the barrier.</i>

00:18.018 --> 00:22.646
<i>We must first eliminate similar players
in other colonies.</i>

00:22.647 --> 00:24.690
<i>Colony contact is key.</i>

00:24.691 --> 00:25.607
1. HANDOVER OF POINTS
2. WITHDRAWAL FROM THE CULLING GAME

00:25.608 --> 00:27.901
<i>The two rules Fushiguro proposed.</i>

00:27.902 --> 00:29.695
<i>Contact methods. Colony entry and exit.</i>

00:29.696 --> 00:30.487
3. COMMUNICATION THROUGH THE BARRIER
4. ENTERING AND LEAVING THE BARRIER

00:30.488 --> 00:34.409
<i>Four rule additions are needed
to resolve this.</i>

00:34.909 --> 00:36.869
<i>Everyone is worn out from Shibuya.</i>

00:36.870 --> 00:38.913
<i>Their bodies and minds
are at their limits.</i>

00:40.665 --> 00:41.791
<i>Mr. Gojo…</i>

00:42.709 --> 00:46.004
<i>I won't have him
kill his best friend twice.</i>

00:46.755 --> 00:48.714
<i>I'll kill Kenjaku.</i>

00:48.715 --> 00:50.842
<i>I'll get the 400 points on my own.</i>

00:57.932 --> 00:59.768
You can come out now.

01:00.268 --> 01:03.896
Let's head north to the barrier's edge.

01:03.897 --> 01:05.564
Carry me.

01:05.565 --> 01:06.441
Hang in there…

01:07.567 --> 01:09.443
Let's rest a moment.

01:09.444 --> 01:13.906
The stadium
was a very powerful sorcerer's territory.

01:13.907 --> 01:17.535
- I don't think anyone will come here yet…
- What's that sound?

01:22.207 --> 01:24.209
Run inside the stadium.

01:26.377 --> 01:27.544
- What?
- Hurry!

01:27.545 --> 01:29.756
- What's going on?
- Help…

01:35.094 --> 01:36.012
Help!

01:41.810 --> 01:43.978
<i>These cockroaches… Are they real?</i>

01:46.064 --> 01:47.065
<i>Damn it.</i>

01:53.279 --> 01:54.530
Rika, drop it!

01:54.531 --> 01:55.406
Move!

01:56.825 --> 01:58.118
Sure thing!

02:11.965 --> 02:14.217
Kogane, is that thing a player too?

02:15.385 --> 02:17.804
Yes, that's Kurourushi.

02:19.180 --> 02:21.516
<i>So cursed spirits can be players too…</i>

02:28.731 --> 02:30.650
FESTERING LIFE SWORD

02:38.032 --> 02:39.117
<i>What?</i>

02:49.085 --> 02:50.086
<i>I'm being watched.</i>

02:51.045 --> 02:54.131
<i>Probably two high-scoring players…</i>

02:54.132 --> 02:56.592
Why do you interfere?

02:56.593 --> 02:58.261
<i>Kurourushi is a cursed spirit.</i>

02:58.845 --> 03:01.930
Why do you kill us?

03:01.931 --> 03:03.432
<i>With a cursed spirit,</i>

03:03.433 --> 03:06.852
<i>I can exorcise it
by firing positive energy</i>

03:06.853 --> 03:08.354
<i>into its body.</i>

03:08.855 --> 03:10.982
I should be the one asking that.

03:11.482 --> 03:12.691
<i>But…</i>

03:12.692 --> 03:15.695
I like the taste of iron!

03:18.615 --> 03:21.325
<i>I don't want the other two to know</i>

03:21.326 --> 03:23.577
<i>I can use Reverse Cursed Technique.</i>

03:23.578 --> 03:26.538
<i>Rika is protecting everyone
at the stadium.</i>

03:26.539 --> 03:28.665
<i>I have to finish Kurourushi without using</i>

03:28.666 --> 03:30.251
<i>Rika or Reverse Cursed Technique!</i>

03:36.424 --> 03:39.969
Blind.

04:53.042 --> 04:55.460
Five points have been added.

04:55.461 --> 04:57.255
<i>So, you can use it?</i>

04:58.256 --> 04:59.382
Reverse Cursed Technique.

05:07.515 --> 05:09.057
<i>What was that?</i>

05:09.058 --> 05:10.101
<i>A strike?</i>

05:20.403 --> 05:23.155
<i>My arm is back… Nothing wrong.</i>

05:23.156 --> 05:26.325
<i>It probably manipulates space,</i>

05:26.326 --> 05:29.578
<i>but maybe it can't crush anyone with it?</i>

05:29.579 --> 05:32.832
<i>It feels like creating a distortion…
like a lens aberration.</i>

05:33.416 --> 05:34.792
My technique perceives the "sky"

05:35.543 --> 05:37.587
as a "surface."

05:39.589 --> 05:41.049
Like this.

05:41.632 --> 05:43.051
<i>She's disclosing her technique.</i>

05:44.010 --> 05:45.803
<i>Come on, hurry up and attack me…</i>

05:46.429 --> 05:48.930
Just asking, but…

05:48.931 --> 05:51.558
you don't mind being killed, right?

05:51.559 --> 05:54.728
I get why the weak fight desperately,

05:54.729 --> 05:58.191
but you can get points whenever you want.

05:58.691 --> 06:01.194
So, why fight so aggressively?

06:01.778 --> 06:02.820
<i>This guy…</i>

06:03.488 --> 06:04.446
What?

06:04.447 --> 06:07.824
Is reincarnating into a sorcerer
just that casual a thing now?

06:07.825 --> 06:11.953
For us, this is a resurrection.
A resurrection!

06:11.954 --> 06:14.331
No one without first-life regrets

06:14.332 --> 06:16.667
would take Kenjaku up on his offer.

06:17.251 --> 06:18.795
<i>God, he's irritating…</i>

06:19.378 --> 06:23.466
The Culling Game is just the first stage
of our second lives.

06:23.966 --> 06:26.928
Kenjaku is behind all this, after all.

06:27.512 --> 06:30.640
You should try to get points
to prepare for any scenario.

06:31.474 --> 06:34.227
Don't you have friends or a partner?

06:36.437 --> 06:37.562
What?

06:37.563 --> 06:41.399
I didn't have friends until recently,

06:41.400 --> 06:43.152
but I still can't relate to you at all.

06:44.195 --> 06:45.862
<i>This feeling…</i>

06:45.863 --> 06:48.533
<i>Like someone is skimming
right along the edge of my anger.</i>

06:49.408 --> 06:53.412
Just because you have regrets,
you kill people hundreds of years later…

06:53.996 --> 06:56.916
Why do you do everything
only for your own sake?

06:57.500 --> 06:58.417
You…

06:59.377 --> 07:00.962
Are you of Fujiwara blood?

07:01.587 --> 07:03.713
What would a clan

07:03.714 --> 07:05.216
like yours understand?

07:15.643 --> 07:16.811
Granite Blast.

07:26.904 --> 07:27.989
<i>Is it Ishigori?</i>

07:28.614 --> 07:31.993
<i>That rooftop, huh? He was quite close.</i>

07:32.577 --> 07:36.079
<i>Even with Rika there, a direct hit</i>

07:36.080 --> 07:39.708
<i>at this level would still kill people.</i>

07:39.709 --> 07:40.751
<i>First is Ishigori.</i>

07:41.586 --> 07:44.045
<i>With Kurourushi and Dhruv gone,</i>

07:44.046 --> 07:46.382
<i>no reason to let Ishigori roam free.</i>

07:46.883 --> 07:48.508
<i>Okkotsu too.</i>

07:48.509 --> 07:49.719
<i>Hunt.</i>

07:51.637 --> 07:53.389
Granite Blast.

08:06.152 --> 08:09.322
Hey. Don't disappoint me now.

08:11.657 --> 08:13.700
He's gone? That's right.

08:13.701 --> 08:15.620
That gap Okkotsu made earlier--

08:20.249 --> 08:22.793
Please fight a little more efficiently.

08:23.461 --> 08:25.879
And will that fill your stomach,

08:25.880 --> 08:26.881
Okkotsu?

08:31.427 --> 08:34.221
Would you tell a kid before a feast

08:34.222 --> 08:37.016
to slow down and eat calmly?

08:38.684 --> 08:40.311
I think I would, actually.

08:41.312 --> 08:44.231
You're right. I might actually say that.

08:44.232 --> 08:45.983
My example was bad.

08:46.484 --> 08:50.488
My first life was about 80% full.

08:51.197 --> 08:55.701
I fought strong opponents
and met some great women.

08:56.202 --> 09:00.164
Honestly, if you ask if I have regrets,
I don't really have any.

09:02.124 --> 09:06.712
This vague kind of thirst
is a real pain, Okkotsu.

09:07.255 --> 09:10.591
Everyone looks at me like,
"What are you unsatisfied with?"

09:12.969 --> 09:16.764
This cigarette… It's a little sweet
after you smoke it.

09:18.349 --> 09:20.225
My life…

09:20.226 --> 09:22.395
had no dessert.

09:23.104 --> 09:24.146
<i>Here he comes.</i>

09:32.989 --> 09:34.782
<i>What am I unsatisfied about?</i>

09:35.825 --> 09:37.326
<i>You already know the answer!</i>

09:44.792 --> 09:48.004
<i>I'm unsatisfied because I'm not full yet!</i>

10:02.393 --> 10:04.645
You'd better not be crushed already!

10:20.870 --> 10:21.996
That hurt.

10:39.680 --> 10:40.765
<i>Okay.</i>

10:47.313 --> 10:49.273
Not calling your <i>shikigami?</i>

10:50.983 --> 10:52.026
I can't do it.

10:52.985 --> 10:54.612
Not while you're rampaging like this.

10:55.196 --> 10:56.781
That's too bad.

11:00.034 --> 11:01.911
<i>He's trying to narrow my options, but…</i>

11:02.995 --> 11:04.121
<i>Head-on…</i>

11:05.998 --> 11:06.957
<i>I'll push straight through!</i>

11:08.542 --> 11:09.709
Sweet!

11:09.710 --> 11:12.588
That's what I'm talking about, Okkotsu!
Then take this!

11:15.841 --> 11:17.760
<i>His cursed energy density just spiked!
Not good!</i>

11:23.349 --> 11:25.267
Well done! Here's your reward.

11:29.814 --> 11:31.189
<i>Oh, wow.</i>

11:31.190 --> 11:33.317
Looks like I overheated.

11:41.951 --> 11:43.993
<i>Not bad, Okkotsu.</i>

11:43.994 --> 11:47.248
<i>Are you my… dessert?</i>

11:54.547 --> 11:55.547
You…

11:55.548 --> 11:57.550
You're incredible!

12:02.721 --> 12:04.306
What I strike is not a person,

12:04.932 --> 12:06.434
but the surface of the sky.

12:08.769 --> 12:09.770
Thin Ice Breaker.

12:13.482 --> 12:15.985
Out of my way! You sick freak!

12:18.654 --> 12:21.532
Shut up, you piece of trash!!

12:27.913 --> 12:29.706
<i>So persistent…</i>

12:29.707 --> 12:33.002
Fine. I decided I would make you suffer.

12:34.670 --> 12:36.212
That hits hard…

12:36.213 --> 12:39.216
First time I've gotten hit
by my own technique…

12:39.758 --> 12:42.385
<i>Reverse Cursed Technique is a problem,</i>

12:42.386 --> 12:44.597
<i>but the cursed energy cost is massive.</i>

12:47.224 --> 12:50.811
<i>I can finally see the bottom, Okkotsu.</i>

12:51.395 --> 12:53.980
<i>Even the finest restaurant disappoints</i>

12:53.981 --> 12:57.693
<i>when it's nearly empty at closing time…</i>

12:59.320 --> 13:01.280
So, it wasn't you after all?

13:06.994 --> 13:08.953
<i>I wanted more distance</i>

13:08.954 --> 13:11.289
<i>from the stadium where everyone is,</i>

13:11.290 --> 13:12.291
<i>but it can't be helped.</i>

13:17.588 --> 13:19.381
Come here, Rika.

13:20.508 --> 13:21.675
Everything.

13:24.762 --> 13:27.055
<i>A</i> shikigami's <i>full manifestation?</i>

13:27.056 --> 13:28.806
<i>How is this possible?</i>

13:28.807 --> 13:31.644
<i>His cursed energy is surging again!</i>

13:32.228 --> 13:34.855
Yuta, which one do you want?

13:35.439 --> 13:38.108
Thank you. That one.

13:39.860 --> 13:42.737
<i>After Rika Orimoto passed on,
the Rika is now</i>

13:42.738 --> 13:47.493
<i>an external technique and a cursed-energy
reserve left behind for Okkotsu.</i>

13:48.077 --> 13:50.453
<i>When connected to Rika via the ring,</i>

13:50.454 --> 13:54.624
<i>he can use stored techniques,
manifest Rika,</i>

13:54.625 --> 13:58.128
<i>and tap into Rika's cursed energy supply,
for that duration.</i>

13:59.088 --> 14:03.175
<i>Maximum connection time is five minutes.</i>

14:05.427 --> 14:06.262
All right.

14:06.971 --> 14:08.138
Let's go.

14:08.847 --> 14:10.140
<i>Don't underestimate me!</i>

14:14.937 --> 14:16.438
<i>Don't move.</i>

14:17.064 --> 14:19.650
<i>The snake's eye and fang… I can't move!</i>

14:25.197 --> 14:26.698
Hey!

14:26.699 --> 14:28.576
That's way too soft!

14:31.036 --> 14:32.370
- Rika!
- Yes.

14:32.371 --> 14:33.247
<i>Come on!</i>

14:34.832 --> 14:35.624
<i>It's not working!</i>

14:41.088 --> 14:42.715
That was close!

14:44.133 --> 14:46.302
Don't get ahead of yourself!

15:15.915 --> 15:18.374
I won't…

15:18.375 --> 15:20.753
forgive you!

15:31.055 --> 15:31.972
<i>What?</i>

15:32.598 --> 15:33.599
Here I go!

15:36.936 --> 15:37.978
Yes!

15:38.520 --> 15:40.481
<i>Even this isn't enough to block it…</i>

15:43.317 --> 15:44.485
Want to play?

16:13.847 --> 16:15.432
Thin Ice Breaker!

16:25.818 --> 16:26.818
FUJIWARA CLAN'S DIRECT ASSASSINATION SQUAD
SUN, MOON AND STARS SQUAD

16:26.819 --> 16:27.819
LIVING IN THE SHADOWS, SELFLESSLY DEVOTED

16:27.820 --> 16:28.737
FORBIDDEN EVEN FROM HAVING A NAME

16:29.905 --> 16:30.947
THE CLAN GAVE ME A NAME

16:30.948 --> 16:31.948
AS A SUBSTITUTE
FOR THE CLANSMAN THEY HAD KILLED

16:31.949 --> 16:32.825
IN ORDER TO EXECUTE ME

16:33.993 --> 16:35.494
Fujiwara!

16:36.495 --> 16:38.371
My appetite…

16:38.372 --> 16:40.207
grows still!

16:41.917 --> 16:43.460
Let's eat up!

16:45.421 --> 16:46.839
It's always you!

16:47.423 --> 16:49.549
Always the ones blocking my path!

16:49.550 --> 16:51.676
Are you that afraid

16:51.677 --> 16:54.346
of me becoming someone?

17:00.644 --> 17:03.939
<i>Dhruv Lakdawalla, defeated by Okkotsu.</i>

17:04.732 --> 17:08.818
<i>His technique treats a</i> shikigami's <i>path</i>

17:08.819 --> 17:12.156
<i>as its domain,
and anything it touches is gouged out.</i>

17:14.658 --> 17:15.783
<i>Is this…</i>

17:15.784 --> 17:17.661
<i>Dhruv's technique?</i>

17:18.162 --> 17:19.287
<i>Could it be that…</i>

17:19.288 --> 17:21.289
<i>Okkotsu's technique is…</i>

17:21.290 --> 17:22.624
<i>Copy?</i>

17:35.429 --> 17:39.265
I don't know what my ancestors
did to you, but

17:39.266 --> 17:41.726
living only for yourself

17:41.727 --> 17:43.811
will reach its limit someday.

17:43.812 --> 17:47.190
Shut up. "Live for someone else."

17:47.191 --> 17:49.234
"You don't need to become anything."

17:50.819 --> 17:53.321
The ones who say that are always…

17:53.322 --> 17:55.866
those who already became someone!

18:11.673 --> 18:15.094
Enough talk! Once you've come this far…

18:16.595 --> 18:18.555
words don't cut it anymore!

18:23.769 --> 18:25.521
- Domain Expansion.
- Domain Expansion.

18:27.981 --> 18:30.983
Give Yuta back!

18:30.984 --> 18:33.861
Even if someone invades the domain later…

18:33.862 --> 18:35.947
I'm not here to drag this out.

18:35.948 --> 18:38.242
Let's end this cleanly!

18:40.202 --> 18:44.163
<i>At that moment, the black devil
of the modern age…</i>

18:44.164 --> 18:48.417
I love the taste of iron!

18:48.418 --> 18:50.337
<i>…sweeps into the domain.</i>

18:53.423 --> 18:55.174
<i>Before going dormant, Kurourushi</i>

18:55.175 --> 18:58.720
<i>had completed parthenogenesis.</i>

18:59.930 --> 19:04.183
<i>Kurourushi still lives as a cursed spirit.</i>

19:04.184 --> 19:07.855
<i>A chaotic three-way domain clash.</i>

19:09.022 --> 19:12.609
<i>And an unplanned intruder.</i>

19:13.193 --> 19:14.570
<i>The domain…</i>

19:17.447 --> 19:19.074
<i>collapses.</i>

19:24.538 --> 19:25.873
<i>Why is Kurourushi here?</i>

19:28.834 --> 19:29.918
<i>Jeez…</i>

19:31.295 --> 19:34.965
<i>Damn! Right after Domain Expansion,
my technique is…</i>

19:41.805 --> 19:45.433
How dare you do that to my arm… Fujiwara?!

19:45.434 --> 19:46.476
That's enough,

19:47.060 --> 19:47.936
Uro.

19:48.437 --> 19:51.231
You weren't invited to this table.

19:53.483 --> 19:55.027
Granite Blast.

19:58.614 --> 20:02.450
<i>Ishigori's technique
is Cursed Energy Discharge.</i>

20:02.451 --> 20:06.913
<i>This extremely simple attack</i>

20:06.914 --> 20:10.125
<i>performs at the same level
even when the technique burns out.</i>

20:18.133 --> 20:19.134
Now then…

20:22.512 --> 20:24.139
Let's sit down to eat,

20:25.766 --> 20:26.892
Okkotsu.

20:28.393 --> 20:30.103
Let's go, Rika.

20:35.192 --> 20:37.443
<i>Only during Rika's full manifestation</i>

20:37.444 --> 20:41.906
<i>can Okkotsu use high-output cursed energy.</i>

20:41.907 --> 20:45.869
<i>However, his peak output
is slightly below Ishigori's.</i>

20:47.371 --> 20:50.581
<i>He charges and releases before Ishigori</i>

20:50.582 --> 20:53.418
<i>can reach maximum output.</i>

20:53.919 --> 20:55.379
<i>That was the plan…</i>

20:56.046 --> 20:58.839
LET'S GO ALL OUT

20:58.840 --> 21:01.759
<i>More than 400 years of longing,</i>

21:01.760 --> 21:04.388
<i>a burning gaze proportional to that thirst</i>

21:05.013 --> 21:09.725
<i>melts the heart of Yuta Okkotsu,</i>

21:09.726 --> 21:13.480
<i>who finds no meaning in fighting itself.</i>

21:14.147 --> 21:15.899
Just this once, all right?

21:34.876 --> 21:38.338
You're seriously sweet, Okkotsu!

21:48.807 --> 21:52.227
Right! Let's do this again and again!

21:56.148 --> 21:58.317
<i>The big one can fire on its own too…</i>

21:58.900 --> 21:59.693
<i>But…</i>

22:01.069 --> 22:03.196
<i>the power is pitiful.</i>

22:04.448 --> 22:07.075
<i>Domain Expansion, plus the fight with me…</i>

22:07.784 --> 22:12.580
<i>I know you're good, but even you
can't recover much anymore.</i>

22:12.581 --> 22:14.415
Time to finish this.

22:14.416 --> 22:17.002
Granite Blast!

22:21.423 --> 22:23.842
<i>Okkotsu's technique…</i>

22:24.551 --> 22:26.845
<i>has already recovered.</i>

22:29.723 --> 22:31.516
<i>Uro's technique?</i>

22:32.059 --> 22:34.560
<i>He's not just a cursed speech user!</i>

22:34.561 --> 22:35.811
<i>That big thing probably</i>

22:35.812 --> 22:39.440
<i>has another technique
different from Okkotsu!</i>

22:39.441 --> 22:43.069
<i>I was wrong! His technique is Copy!</i>

22:43.070 --> 22:46.322
<i>But there have to be conditions.
When were the conditions met?</i>

22:46.323 --> 22:47.991
<i>While I wasn't watching?</i>

22:48.617 --> 22:50.368
<i>Could it be unconditional?</i>

22:54.623 --> 22:56.374
<i>Was it that moment?</i>

22:57.084 --> 22:58.543
Thin Ice Breaker!

23:09.638 --> 23:10.514
<i>Five minutes is up.</i>

23:11.139 --> 23:14.392
<i>Rika and Okkotsu's connection is severed.</i>

23:20.607 --> 23:22.901
Yuta!

23:26.071 --> 23:27.447
I didn't know.

23:31.535 --> 23:34.871
<i>That there's still something left
after going all out.</i>

23:37.624 --> 23:41.044
<i>So this… is the dessert!</i>

24:02.941 --> 24:04.693
<i>That's enough.</i>

24:08.196 --> 24:08.989
<i>What?</i>

24:09.823 --> 24:11.283
<i>What's his aim here?</i>

24:28.425 --> 24:30.760
<i>This is… my own…</i>

24:33.930 --> 24:36.765
<i>Back then, he used Uro's technique</i>

24:36.766 --> 24:38.977
<i>to redirect the trajectory!</i>

24:42.272 --> 24:43.899
Thank you.

24:50.655 --> 24:52.407
I'm full.

25:10.592 --> 25:13.136
You're too soft, Okkotsu.

25:13.970 --> 25:15.888
And I don't mean that as a compliment.

25:15.889 --> 25:17.890
Letting a sorcerer live after a fight--

25:17.891 --> 25:20.893
There's nothing to gain from it.

25:20.894 --> 25:22.020
Uro said the same thing.

25:22.687 --> 25:24.773
She survived?

25:26.483 --> 25:30.403
Well, a blast after Domain Expansion
couldn't be too strong.

25:30.987 --> 25:33.739
She was going on about something.

25:33.740 --> 25:34.950
A lover's quarrel?

25:35.450 --> 25:37.077
Something like that.

25:37.577 --> 25:39.370
Don't be so difficult about it.

25:39.371 --> 25:42.457
There's nothing I can say to her.

25:43.458 --> 25:45.794
Anything I say would feel like violence.

25:46.670 --> 25:48.755
Because I've been so fortunate.

25:50.090 --> 25:53.551
If you say so. I don't really get it, but…

25:54.844 --> 25:56.179
Regardless,

25:56.972 --> 25:58.390
please give me your points.

26:01.559 --> 26:03.269
I see.

26:03.270 --> 26:06.648
Without this,
you would have killed us, wouldn't you?

26:08.233 --> 26:10.068
Hard to say.

26:12.946 --> 26:15.614
Thank my teammates instead.

26:15.615 --> 26:18.367
POINTS

26:18.368 --> 26:22.121
THANKS TO POINT TRANSFER
FROM TAKAKO URO AND RYU ISHIGORI

26:22.122 --> 26:24.624
YUTA OKKOTSU, POINTS OWNED 190

26:27.294 --> 26:30.046
<i>You're the one who'll hit your limit.</i>

26:33.925 --> 26:35.552
I have seen it.

26:39.514 --> 26:41.057
<i>What transcends even the horizon</i>

26:41.641 --> 26:44.311
<i>of sorcerers, spirits, and the powerful…</i>

26:45.645 --> 26:47.814
<i>An overwhelming sense of self.</i>

26:48.398 --> 26:49.816
<i>A calamity…</i>

26:50.650 --> 26:51.901
<i>that heeds nothing else.</i>

26:57.907 --> 27:00.869
‎TO BE CONTINUED
